***** Course Description *****
This participatory seminar focuses on the knowledge and skills necessary for
teaching science and engineering in higher education. This course is designed
for graduate students interested in an academic career, and anyone else
interested in teaching. Topics include theories of adult learning; course
development; promoting active learning, problem-solving, and critical thinking
in students; communicating with a diverse student body; using educational
technology to further learning; lecturing; creating effective tests and
assignments; and assessment and evaluation. Students research and present a
relevant topic of particular interest. The subject is appropriate for both
novices and those with teaching experience.
